# Domain Layer Rules

## Core Principle
Domain is fully isolated.

- MUST have zero external dependencies
- MUST NOT depend on any other layer

---

## Allowed

- Entities
- Value Objects
- Repository interfaces
- Domain exceptions

---

## Forbidden

### Imports
- application/**
- infrastructure/**
- presentation/**
- NestJS
- Prisma / ORM
- HTTP types (Request, Response, DTOs)

### Usage
- Decorators (@Injectable, @Inject, etc.)
- External services or SDKs

---

## Entities

### Required
- Must have identity
- Must contain domain logic only

### Forbidden
- Infrastructure logic
- Persistence logic

---

## Value Objects

### Required
- Must be immutable
- Must validate input in constructor
- Must implement equality

---

## Repositories

### Required
- Interfaces only
- Use domain types only (Entities, Value Objects)

### Forbidden
- Implementations
- ORM types

---

## Exceptions

- Must represent domain errors only
- No HTTP or framework exceptions

---

## File Naming

- entities → `*.entity.ts`
- value-objects → `*.value-object.ts`
- repositories → `*.repository.ts`
- exceptions → `*.exception.ts`